# Fix-shore (`shore fix`): a SEPARATE, deliberate pass that
# re-tiles existing shore to close the discontinuities the single-pass
# loop-walk leaves on a steep coast. It is never auto-chained onto the
# auto passes, and is hard-bounded, so it can never make editing hang.
# Run: cargo run -- --script scripts/shore-fix.script --headless

new 24 18 GREEN 3
tile GLa000

# A steep sine coast (land below the wave).
stroke begin
paint 0 9
paint 0 10
paint 0 11
